Aneka Tambang, Mandiri, Medco Energi: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-05T01:37:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/aneka-tambang-mandiri-medco-energi-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.4 percent to 4,122.09.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures plunged 5.8 percent to
$86.63 a barrel in  New York  yesterday, erasing all of its gains
for 2011. Oil was last at $85.77 a barrel in after-hours
trading.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 1 percent to 2,475 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, sank 5.9
percent to 240 rupiah.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ): Indonesia’s second-largest
nickel producer said it named Goldman Sachs Group Inc., PT Bank
Mandiri (BMRI IJ) and PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI IJ) as
among financial arrangers to help it fund a $1.6 billion
ferronickel project in East Halmahera in  Indonesia ’s North
Maluku province.  Aneka Tambang was unchanged at 2,000 rupiah. Bank Mandiri,
Indonesia’s biggest bank by assets, rose 0.7 percent to 7,700
rupiah and Bank Rakyat, the largest by revenue, dropped 1.4
percent to 7,100 rupiah.  PT International Nickel Indonesia (INCO IJ): The company’s
President Director Tony Wenas plans to resign in September,
Kontan reported, citing a person it didn’t identify. Wenas, who
was named president director in March last year, declined to
comment when asked by Kontan, the report said. International
Nickel, Indonesia’s largest producer of the metal, declined 1.2
percent to 4,075 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  